description:
&lt;p&gt;VIRTUAL WARD Frail elderly- Community but not as you know it!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work as part of HSJ award winning team, who are innovative integrated team of health and social care who have both national and international recognition and is shortlisted for a Health Service Journal award? Then read on&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Summary of most important Experience/Skills/Qualifications required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a developing service, delivering medically challenging care to patients in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a friendly fun loving team, based in a modern environment at St Luke’s Hospital Bradford and an opportunity to travel across Bradford and its boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team consists of 3 consultants, Advance nurse practitioner, community specialist nurses, independent prescribers, pharmacist, ward sisters, staff nurses, and therapist and rehabilitation assistants. There is a clear development pathway for nurses new to the team. We offer and excellent preceptorship and continued mentorship to enable the development of skills and competence required. We welcome applications from candidates who are ready to enhance their existing assessment skills and keen to experience community work, we also welcome applications from newly qualified nurses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
